<h3><strong>Ranbir Kapoor-Alia Bhatt&rsquo;s new luxury mansion is now Bandra&rsquo;s new crown</strong></h3>

<p>Located at Pali Hill&rsquo;s platinum belt, it is a 6-storey mansion with rooftop gardens and vine-draped balconies. The mansion has been under construction for years, and Ranbir Kapoor, Alia Bhatt, and Neetu Kapoor have overseen every design and architect. It is now Bandra&rsquo;s crown as the royal mansion has beaten Shah Rukh Khan&rsquo;s popular residence.</p>

<p>According to Business Today, the property is worth Rs 250 crore, making it the costliest celebrity residence in Mumbai, beating Shah Rukh Khan&rsquo;s Rs 200 crore worth Mannat and Amitabh Bachchan&rsquo;s Jalsa of Rs 120 crore.</p>

<p>Interestingly, the newly constructed home is registered in Ranbir-Alia&rsquo;s baby girl&rsquo;s name, Raha Kapoor, which adds an emotional touch to the property.&nbsp;</p>

<h3><strong>History of Ranbir Kapoor&rsquo;s new bungalow</strong></h3>

<p>The property has a long history! The plot on which <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/exclusives/exclusive-ranbir-kapoor-gears-up-for-6-feature-films-from-2026-to-2029-from-ramayana-to-animal-park-dhoom-4-1358140">Ranbir Kapoor</a>&rsquo;s new mansion is situated originally belonged to Raj Kapoor and Krishan Raj Kapoor (Ranbir&rsquo;s grandparents). It was inherited by Rishi Kapoor and Neetu Kapoor in the 1980s and has now been registered under the name of the Kapoor clan&rsquo;s future generation, Raha.&nbsp;</p>

<p>While the mansion is almost ready, there is still work left. The couple is expected to shift to their luxury residence soon on an auspicious date.</p>

